/notes/The-Epistle-of-Ignatius-of-Antioc.text: become the disciple of Him who gave Himself for us, an offering and sacrifice to God
has in all things refreshed me, as the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ shall also refresh him
unanimous obedience you may be perfectly joined together in the same mind, and in the same judgment, and may all speak the same thing concerning the same thing
For if the prayer of one or two possesses
For we ought to receive every one whom the Master of the house sends to be over His household
as being stones of the temple of the Father, prepared for the building of God the Father
making use of the Holy Spirit as a rope, while your faith was the means by which you ascended, and your love the way which led up to God
Be meek in response to their wrath, humble in opposition to their boasting: to their blasphemies return your prayers; in contrast to their error, be stedfast in the faith
if you perfectly possess that faith and love towards Christ Jesus
For the beginning is faith, and the end is love.
The tree is made manifest by its fruit;
that we may be His temples
If, then, those who do this as respects the flesh have suffered death,
For this end did the Lord allow the ointment to be poured upon His head,
Let my spirit be counted as nothing for the sake of the cross, which is a stumbling-block to those that do not believe, but to us salvation and life eternal.
Where is the wise man? Where the disputer? Where is the boasting of those who are styled prudent?
